HEADWORD: nut sedge
<hw>nut sedge</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a
widely distributed perennial sedge (<spn>Cyperus rotundus</spn>) having
small edible nutlike tubers; also called <altname>nut
grass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nutgrass, nut grass, <spn>Cyperus
rotundus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
